---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import CTASection from "../components/CTASection.astro";
---
<MainLayout
  title="Utilities Solutions | KUEM"
  description="Smart water and gas metering, infrastructure monitoring, and integrations for utility operations."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Main revenue driver</p>
        <h1>Utility IoT solutions built for integration, reliability, and scale.</h1>
        <p>
          KUEM helps water and gas utilities modernize metering and infrastructure monitoring without disrupting existing
          systems.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="panel">
        <h2>Common utility pain points we address</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Delayed fault detection and manual reads</li>
          <li>Data silos between telemetry, SCADA, and billing</li>
          <li>Non-revenue water and leakage detection challenges</li>
          <li>Limited visibility across distributed assets</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container grid-3">
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Smart Water Metering</h2>
        <p>Remote reads, flow anomaly alerts, and district-level analytics to reduce non-revenue water.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>LoRaWAN and NB-IoT support</li>
          <li>Consumption profiles and leak indicators</li>
          <li>Billing export automation</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Smart Gas Metering</h2>
        <p>Secure gas metering telemetry with alarms for pressure deviations and potential leakage events.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>NB-IoT optimization for deep indoor coverage</li>
          <li>Tamper and anomaly event handling</li>
          <li>Accurate, frequent meter data delivery</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Infrastructure Monitoring</h2>
        <p>Condition and performance visibility for pumping stations, valves, reservoirs, and remote sites.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Threshold and trend-based alerting</li>
          <li>Maintenance workflow triggers</li>
          <li>Operational dashboards for field teams</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container split">
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Integration-ready architecture</h2>
        <p>
          Nexavia connects metering and sensor data into your current ecosystem through open APIs, export adapters, and
          configurable workflows.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>SCADA connectivity for operations teams</li>
          <li>Billing and ERP integration for commercial processes</li>
          <li>Role-based data access for cross-functional users</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Pilot-first approach</h2>
        <p>
          Start with a focused pilot that validates data quality, integration performance, and operational value before
          full deployment.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>90-day pilot design</li>
          <li>Joint KPI definition and reporting</li>
          <li>Scalable rollout plan based on results</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection title="Plan your utility pilot" description="Discuss your service area, integration stack, and rollout priorities with KUEM specialists." />
</MainLayout>
